they will be officially approved

47
00:03:47,333 --> 00:03:49,875
to join the organization.

48
00:03:49,958 --> 00:03:51,208
Once that happens,

49
00:03:51,291 --> 00:03:53,083
even Wisemel with
all of his underhanded dealings,

50
00:03:53,166 --> 00:03:54,708
can't touch them.

51
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:56,708
So this will be
his last opportunity.

52
00:03:56,791 --> 00:03:58,208
I suspect he'll take it.

53
00:03:58,291 --> 00:03:59,458
Isaac...

54
00:03:59,541 --> 00:04:01,083
You're still suspicious
of that guy?

55
00:04:01,166 --> 00:04:03,708
All of those shootings
that happened the other day,

56
00:04:03,791 --> 00:04:05,458
and Muroto's murder.

57
00:04:05,541 --> 00:04:08,333
Wisemel's the only one
who would stand to benefit.

58
00:04:08,416 --> 00:04:10,875
So we need to watch him
carefully.

59
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:12,416
The meeting will be held
in a conference room

60
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:13,791
with a large window

61
00:04:13,875 --> 00:04:16,333
on the fifth floor
of the Atrium Hotel.

62
00:04:16,416 --> 00:04:18,708
So we're putting
the prey on display.

63
00:04:18,791 --> 00:04:20,333
It shouldn't be difficult
to find a spot

64
00:04:20,416 --> 00:04:22,083
with a clear view
of the meeting.

65
00:04:22,166 --> 00:04:23,166
You really think it's smart

66
00:04:23,250 --> 00:04:25,416
to keep using
the Godo family as bait?

67
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,541
If it works, then yes.

68
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:32,875
However, I haven't
forgotten what a gamble it is

69
00:04:32,958 --> 00:04:34,958
without my one and only...

70
00:04:35,041 --> 00:04:36,375
my Phantom.

71
00:04:43,875 --> 00:04:45,833
Oh, good!
He's home!

72
00:04:45,916 --> 00:04:47,791
I hope you had a good day.

73
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:50,458
Like any other.

74
00:04:50,541 --> 00:04:51,875
Wait just a sec,

75
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,958
I'll run into the kitchen
and reheat you some soup.

76
00:05:04,208 --> 00:05:05,208
Hey, Cal!

77
00:05:12,916 --> 00:05:15,250
I found this when I was
cleaning up the place.

78
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:16,500
Did you disassemble it?

79
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:18,333
Yeah.
Sorry.

80
00:05:18,416 --> 00:05:19,625
I'll fix it.

81
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:25,208
So tell me...

82
00:05:25,291 --> 00:05:27,083
you good with machines
and stuff?

83
00:05:27,166 --> 00:05:29,166
I've always kinda liked
taking stuff apart

84
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:30,958
and putting it back together.

85
00:05:31,041 --> 00:05:32,125
I guess I just want to know

86
00:05:32,208 --> 00:05:34,000
how everything works
or somethin'.

87
00:05:39,750 --> 00:05:41,416
Okay.
It's ready.

88
00:05:41,500 --> 00:05:42,666
Good.

89
00:05:42,750 --> 00:05:43,750
Now put it back
where you found it.

90
00:05:43,833 --> 00:05:44,791
Got it.

91
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:49,125
Is that work?

92
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:50,375
It is.

93
00:05:50,458 --> 00:05:51,333
Do you wanna sit down
and help me figure out

94
00:05:51,416 --> 00:05:52,583
what I should do?

95
00:05:52,666 --> 00:05:55,125
Oh yeah, totally!

96
00:05:55,208 --> 00:05:57,041
What is it?

97
00:05:57,125 --> 00:05:58,458
Look here.

98
00:05:58,541 --> 00:06:00,833
The target'll be on the fifth
floor of this building.

99
00:06:00,916 --> 00:06:02,416
So I gotta assume
the sniper will be shooting

100
00:06:02,500 --> 00:06:03,291
from this side.

101
00:06:04,666 --> 00:06:06,083
Are you the sniper?

102
00:06:06,166 --> 00:06:07,083
No, I'm not.

103
00:06:07,166 --> 00:06:08,333
Someone else.

104
00:06:08,416 --> 00:06:10,333
And I don't know who yet.

105
00:06:10,416 --> 00:06:13,541
Our job is to try and figure
out where this guy is gonna be.

106
00:06:13,625 --> 00:06:15,000
Gotcha.

107
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:16,791
But he can't do it
from just anywhere.

108
00:06:16,875 --> 00:06:17,875
He'll choose the place

109
00:06:17,958 --> 00:06:20,208
that best meets
the criteria of the hit.

110
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:22,291
Whaddaya mean?

111
00:06:22,375 --> 00:06:24,833
Well, the place will need to be
high enough to see the target,

112
00:06:24,916 --> 00:06:27,750
but still keep the shooter
out of the line of sight.

113
00:06:27,833 --> 00:06:29,458
Like maybe a roof top
or somethin'?

114
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:30,541
I don't see why not.

115
00:06:30,625 --> 00:06:32,125
Well then, what about here?

116
00:06:32,208 --> 00:06:34,750
I don't know,
it seems too close.

117
00:06:34,833 --> 00:06:36,291
If the target can
catch a glimpse of the shooter,

118
00:06:36,375 --> 00:06:37,791
then the jig's up.

119
00:06:37,875 --> 00:06:39,083
The guy's gonna
have to settle down

120
00:06:39,166 --> 00:06:40,708
at least 400 yards away.

121
00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:42,833
Four hundred yards!

122
00:06:42,916 --> 00:06:44,708
He can still hit the target
from there?

123
00:06:44,791 --> 00:06:47,000
Depending on equipment
and skills,

124
00:06:47,083 --> 00:06:49,916
he could get a good shot off
from up to 800 yards away.

125
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:50,708
Whoa!

126
00:06:52,541 --> 00:06:55,791
So like, he could
basically be anywhere.

127
00:06:55,875 --> 00:06:57,291
How are we gonna
narrow it down?

128
00:06:57,375 --> 00:06:58,750
I don't know,

129
00:06:58,833 --> 00:07:00,541
but there are a whole
lotta places to choose from.

130
00:07:02,916 --> 00:07:05,166
It's your homework
before bedtime.

131
00:07:05,250 --> 00:07:06,416
Now let's eat dinner.

132
00:07:12,625 --> 00:07:14,333
You figure out the situation?

133
00:07:14,416 --> 00:07:16,791
I did.
It's all good.

134
00:07:16,875 --> 00:07:18,458
Don't you worry.

135
00:07:18,541 --> 00:07:20,000
Don't screw this up.

136
00:07:20,083 --> 00:07:23,250
You do, I'll cut off your balls
and feed 'em to my dogs.

137
00:07:23,333 --> 00:07:24,791
I understand, sir.

138
00:07:29,083 --> 00:07:30,833
What's the matter?

139
00:07:30,916 --> 00:07:32,666
I was wondering...

140
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:35,541
Is it hard to aim
from a really high place?

141
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:37,416
Or like uncomfortable?

142
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:39,625
What makes you say that?

143
00:07:39,708 --> 00:07:43,208
The way you hold the gun,
when you point it so far down,

144
00:07:43,291 --> 00:07:46,166
it seems hard,
a little unnatural.

145
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:49,583
What is it?
Does that sound stupid?

146
00:07:49,666 --> 00:07:51,000
Not at all.

147
00:07:51,083 --> 00:07:52,625
You gotta good point.

148
00:07:52,708 --> 00:07:55,291
It is pretty hard to shoot
with your body posed that way.

149
00:07:55,375 --> 00:07:57,083
It seems like it to me.

150
00:07:57,166 --> 00:07:58,708
So maybe we can forget about
looking for him

151
00:07:58,791 --> 00:08:00,583
in really high places.

152
00:08:00,666 --> 00:08:03,083
He'll probably wanna be
on the same level as the target.

153
00:08:03,166 --> 00:08:05,916
Somewhere that's gonna be
easy for him to see it.

154
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:07,625
So if we think of it that way,

155
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:09,708
we cut down the number
of places he could be.

156
00:08:10,958 --> 00:08:12,208
I think you're
on to something.

157
00:08:12,291 --> 00:08:13,541
So I'm right?

158
00:08:13,625 --> 00:08:15,416
You're doing pretty good so far.

159
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:17,166
That's awesome!

160
00:08:17,250 --> 00:08:19,791
We'll do the rest of the work
when we get to the site.

161
00:08:19,875 --> 00:08:21,375
Hope you don't mind
coming with me.

162
00:08:21,458 --> 00:08:24,166
Omigod, really?

163
00:08:24,250 --> 00:08:26,000
I'm going somewhere with you!

164
00:08:26,083 --> 00:08:27,666
Don't forget,
this is still work.

165
00:08:27,750 --> 00:08:28,833
Yes!

166
00:08:31,541 --> 00:08:32,708
Sorry to bother you.

167
00:08:36,458 --> 00:08:38,083
I thought you should know
Muroto's body

168
00:08:38,166 --> 00:08:40,666
went back to Japan
earlier today.

169
00:08:40,750 --> 00:08:42,375
Kakinuma and Tsuzuki
are flying in

170
00:08:42,458 --> 00:08:44,041
on the redeye tonight,

171
00:08:44,125 --> 00:08:45,833
and are bringing
all of their men with them.

172
00:08:45,916 --> 00:08:47,500
Any word on guns?

173
00:08:47,583 --> 00:08:48,875
I had Giuseppe get them.

174
00:08:48,958 --> 00:08:51,375
They'll be in hand
by tomorrow afternoon.

175
00:08:51,458 --> 00:08:53,375
Well, he'd better
come through for us.

176
00:08:55,083 --> 00:08:56,833
Goodbye drink to Muroto?

177
00:08:56,916 --> 00:08:57,875
Yeah.

178
00:08:59,250 --> 00:09:01,416
You should really join me
on this one.

179
00:09:05,333 --> 00:09:06,666
May he rest in peace.

180
00:09:10,125 --> 00:09:11,833
Sonofabitch Muroto.

181
00:09:11,916 --> 00:09:13,791
Died without
finishing the bottle.

182
00:09:13,875 --> 00:09:15,458
He's not the only one.

183
00:09:15,541 --> 00:09:18,875
Homura and Shinjou
got taken outta the game too.

184
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:20,625
I've gotten
five of my men killed

185
00:09:20,708 --> 00:09:22,708
in this foreign shithole
since we got here.

186
00:09:22,791 --> 00:09:24,875
Millions of dollars
are at stake.

187
00:09:24,958 --> 00:09:27,916
It's natural
for it to turn into a war.

188
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:30,333
I'm sure that every one of them
understood that.

189
00:09:30,416 --> 00:09:31,833
Yes, it's war.

190
00:09:31,916 --> 00:09:33,000
That's why
I'm pissed at myself

191
00:09:33,083 --> 00:09:34,916
for letting Muroto
go out without a gun.

192
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:36,541
What the hell
was I thinking?

193
00:09:36,625 --> 00:09:37,750
I should've known better.

194
00:09:39,250 --> 00:09:41,625
Goddammit, I know
Inferno's behind all this,

195
00:09:41,708 --> 00:09:43,458
and they're gonna pay for it.

196
00:09:43,541 --> 00:09:45,000
They owe us bodies.

197
00:09:45,083 --> 00:09:46,500
Speaking of Inferno...

198
00:09:46,583 --> 00:09:47,750
listen.

199
00:09:47,833 --> 00:09:49,125
I've got some
fairly deep suspicions

200
00:09:49,208 --> 00:09:50,541
of that Claudia woman.

201
00:09:51,625 --> 00:09:53,083
Well, let me hear 'em.

202
00:09:53,166 --> 00:09:55,750
Our involvement
in her little caper last year

203
00:09:55,833 --> 00:09:58,958
puts the two of us
directly in the crosshairs.

204
00:09:59,041 --> 00:10:00,958
If push comes to shove
on this matter,

205
00:10:01,041 --> 00:10:04,291
I suspect she'll find a way
to take us out of the equation.

206
00:10:04,375 --> 00:10:05,208
Listen, Shiga.

207
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:08,416
In this case,
I gotta tell ya,

208
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:10,500
Claudia's an innocent woman.

209
00:10:10,583 --> 00:10:12,041
You have any proof to that?

210
00:10:12,125 --> 00:10:13,541
Proof?

211
00:10:13,625 --> 00:10:15,000
Shiga...

212
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:16,875
You know
what the tattoo on my back is.

213
00:10:18,208 --> 00:10:21,208
Five colored spheres
and a rising dragon.

214
00:10:21,291 --> 00:10:24,500
The dragon on my back,
he feels it.

215
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:27,125
That woman...

216
00:10:27,208 --> 00:10:30,250
she carries
the same dragon on her back.

217
00:10:30,333 --> 00:10:33,916
The two of us share
the same kind of spirit,

218
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,958
a dragon,
that gains control of heaven

219
00:10:36,041 --> 00:10:39,416
by first conquering
the spheres.

220
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:42,916
So, I think I should leave
the matter in her hands for now.

221
00:10:43,000 --> 00:10:44,833
It's hard to explain.

222
00:10:44,916 --> 00:10:47,333
This probably
sounds crazy to you.

223
00:10:47,416 --> 00:10:49,583
You've always been
the rational one.

224
00:10:52,208 --> 00:10:53,583
That said,

225
00:10:53,666 --> 00:10:56,291
I'm counting on your wisdom
to pull me through this.

226
00:10:56,375 --> 00:10:57,875
You need to trust me.

227
00:10:57,958 --> 00:11:01,208
But more importantly,
you need to trust my spirit.

228
00:11:01,291 --> 00:11:03,041
If you insist that much of me,

229
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:06,916
I suppose.

230
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,041
But I can't help
but to keep one eye open.

231
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:27,875
Thanks for coming.

232
00:11:34,083 --> 00:11:36,166
Wonder what Inferno's
gonna think about this.

233
00:11:36,250 --> 00:11:37,583
Can't wait to find out.

234
00:11:43,875 --> 00:11:45,500
Come on, Cal!

235
00:11:45,583 --> 00:11:47,250
Yeah, I'll be right there!

236
00:11:53,291 --> 00:11:55,291
Since we're going out,
I wanted to look cute.

237
00:11:57,375 --> 00:11:58,500
Shall we?

238
00:11:58,583 --> 00:11:59,625
Let's!

239
00:12:06,916 --> 00:12:08,833
Okay,
that's the target building.

240
00:12:08,916 --> 00:12:10,541
First we need to
narrow down the places

241
00:12:10,625 --> 00:12:12,625
that meet the criteria
we talked about,

242
00:12:12,708 --> 00:12:13,875
then we walk the streets

243
00:12:13,958 --> 00:12:16,083
and identify
the most viable location.

244
00:12:16,166 --> 00:12:17,291
How do we do that?

245
00:12:17,375 --> 00:12:18,916
Look for a weather vane.

246
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:19,958
How come?

247
00:12:20,041 --> 00:12:21,458
Part of the preparation.

248
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:22,791
Without it,
even the most skilled pros

249
00:12:22,875 --> 00:12:25,458
couldn't pull off
a difficult sniping.

250
00:12:25,541 --> 00:12:26,875
Look around,

251
00:12:26,958 --> 00:12:28,500
there are tall buildings
everywhere.

252
00:12:33,458 --> 00:12:34,541
It's windy.

253
00:12:34,625 --> 00:12:36,083
That's right.

254
00:12:36,166 --> 00:12:38,875
A strong wind can screw up
what should be a clear shot.

255
00:12:38,958 --> 00:12:40,208
You don't wanna miss.

256
00:12:40,291 --> 00:12:43,083
So you have to make sure
that you can see the wind.

257
00:12:43,166 --> 00:12:45,041
Yeah, but you can't
see the wind.

258
00:12:47,250 --> 00:12:49,000
So, you use that.

259
00:12:49,083 --> 00:12:51,333
Yeah, like a lotta snipers
will put up something like this

260
00:12:51,416 --> 00:12:54,000
that'll catch the wind
and tell us what it's doing.

261
00:12:54,083 --> 00:12:55,791
Cool, we gonna walk around

262
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:57,791
and look for something
hanging like that?

